text: Khan Tengri, named after the Sky God Tengri of the Turkic peoples ancient Tengrism pagan religion, is a mountain in the Tian Shan range in Kyrgyzstan and Kazakhstan. Khan Tengri is the highest mountain in Kazakhstan. The first people to reach the top were Mikhail Pogrebetsky and his team, in 1931. == References == Category:Mountains of Kyrgyzstan Category:Geography of Kazakhstan
